A Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) governorship aspirant for the November 16, election in Kogi, Alhaji Aminu Suleiman, has promised to provide quality technical education to make the youths employers of labour rather than job seekers if given the opportunity. Suleiman, who made the promise while speaking at a media parley for gubernatorial aspirants in Kogi State organised by the state chapter of the Nigeria Union of Journalists (NUJ), said free medicare for pregnant women and the aged would be pursued. The PDP aspirant assured that the state would witness purposeful leadership that would guarantee quality social and economic advancement. He also promised overall human development that would positively meet the yearnings and aspirations of the people. More aspirants pick Kogi APC gov forms 2019: Kogi PDP assures aspirants of fair play We’ll spring surprises in Kogi, Bayelsa polls – LP Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin